Suppose you are asked the following question:
&ldquo;You have a sequence \(X = {X_1, &hellip;, X_N}\) of independently and identically distributed random variables drawn from the same unknown distribution. How would you estimate the variance of the sample median?&rdquo;
This question was posed to me in a recent data science interview. At the time I didn&rsquo;t know the answer because I was pretty unfamiliar with computational statistics. But now, as a form of self-atonement, I want to answer this question in detail.
